Thought I would share the snippet we are using for selecting the best stream based on current bitrate estimate.

``` java
    /**
     * Return the highest quality stream based on the current bitrate estimate
     *
     * @param playlist - Master playlist
     * @param variants - Playback variants sorted in descending bitrate order
     * @return The variant index of the best available stream
     */
    @Override
    protected int getDefaultVariantIndex(HlsMasterPlaylist playlist, Variant[] variants,
      BandwidthMeter bandwidthMeter) {
        long bitrateEstimate = bandwidthMeter.getBitrateEstimate();

        if (bitrateEstimate == BandwidthMeter.NO_ESTIMATE) {
            return super.getDefaultVariantIndex(playlist, variants, bandwidthMeter);
        }

        int defaultVariantIndex = variants.length - 1;
        for (int i = variants.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            Format variantFormat = variants[i].format;
            if (variantFormat.bitrate < bitrateEstimate) {
                defaultVariantIndex = i;
            }
        }

        return  defaultVariantIndex;
    }
```

